"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850245","HM Treasury","false","2018-03-06","<p>HMT has not made a formal assessment of the cost of nationalisations. However, in my speech to Policy Exchange on 30 January I referenced a report by the Centre for Policy Studies which suggests that the cost of renationalising energy, water, rail and PFI could be over £170 billion.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850245/answer",,,,,,"2018-03-06T13:14:34.247Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850245/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850245/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-02-26","Nationalisation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate his Department has made of the cost of renationalising British industries.","false","Biography information for Mr Ranil Jayawardena","North East Hampshire","Mr Ranil Jayawardena","129813"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850246","HM Treasury","false","2018-03-06","<p>The government recognises that, in the long-term, revenues from a number of the current transport taxes may decline as vehicles use less liquid fuels. HM Treasury keeps all transport taxes under review, as it does with all taxes, and if the Chancellor decides to make changes, he will announce them at fiscal events.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850246/answer",,,,,,"2018-03-06T17:48:42.233Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850246/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850246/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-02-26","Fuels: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, If he will make it his policy to reduce duties on petrol as people switch to electric cars.","false","Biography information for Mr Ranil Jayawardena","North East Hampshire","Mr Ranil Jayawardena","129814"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850247","HM Treasury","false","2018-03-06","<p>This government is committed to delivering modern and efficient infrastructure across every part of the country.</p><p> </p><p>Access to Superfast broadband in Hampshire has risen from 56.7% to 93.8% since 2010, and we have confirmed the introduction of a regulatory Universal Service Obligation, to give everyone in the UK the right to request a broadband connection with speeds of at least 10 Mbps by 2020.</p><p> </p><p>Next month work will start on upgrading the M27 smart motorway scheme to link it with the M3 smart motorway scheme. Hampshire County Council has received LEP funding to support transport schemes that drive economic growth and house-building such as the Stubbington and Bordon/Whitehall Bypasses.</p><p> </p><p>Major cities in England will be able to bid into the competitive element of the £1.7 billion transport fund launched at budget to drive productivity in our great cities, and up to £1 billion is available for local authorities to borrow from at a new discounted interest rate to support high-value infrastructure projects.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850247/answer",,,,,,"2018-03-06T15:00:15.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850247/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/850247/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2018-02-26","Infrastructure: Hampshire","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps he is taking to support regional infrastructure development in Hampshire.","false","Biography information for Mr Ranil Jayawardena","North East Hampshire","Mr Ranil Jayawardena","129815"
