"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/846948","Department for Education","false","2018-03-02","<p>44 providers allocated funding from the Adult Education Budget received an inadequate outcome following their latest financial health assessment by the Education and Skills Funding Agency (ESFA).</p><p>The ESFA does not have direct relationships with subcontractors and does not visit them. The contractor is responsible for all the actions of its subcontractors connected to or arising out of the delivery of the services, which it sub-contracts.</p><p>Since 1 April 2017, the ESFA has received a total of 33 reports covering allegations of irregular financial and/or delivery activity. This includes sub-contracted provision.</p>","Guildford","Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/846948/answer",,,,,"129123 ; 129124","2018-03-02T14:25:53.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/846948/answer","Biography information for Anne Milton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/846948/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2018-02-22","Adult Education: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many providers allocated funding from the Adult Education Budget received an inadequate outcome following their latest financial health assessment by the Education and Skills Funding Agency.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","129122"
